-- Google Beats Toyota, Sony as Most Favored Job-Change Destination in Japan
-- Pavel Alpeyev
-- 2010-06-23T01:00:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/google-beats-toyota-sony-as-most-favored-job-change-destination-in-japan.html

          
          
             Google Inc.  beat  Toyota Motor Corp. 
and  Sony Corp.  as Japan’s most popular destination for people
seeking to change jobs this year, according to an on-line survey
by recruitment services company Intelligence Ltd.  
 Toyota, which ranked first for the past two years, fell to
third place, while Sony kept its second-place ranking, according
to the Tokyo-based recruiter’s  website . Google, based in
Mountain View, California, was third in 2009, it said.  
 The survey’s 5,000 participants rated Google as offering
the most challenging and technical working environment, while
Toyota was voted the most secure place of employment. For female
respondents, the search engine operator was second to cosmetics
maker  Shiseido Co.  as the most desirable job-change destination,
according to the survey.  
 Google is currently hiring for sales, marketing, operations,
and public relations positions at its Tokyo office, according to
the company’s website.  
